The paper deals with a SLAM method that uses sensor fusion and dense map representation, which are common topics in robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of probabilistic models and optimization techniques, which are relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper addresses the issue of real-time operation, which is a concern in systems and control (cs.SY).
